&lt;h2 id=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://leetcode.com/problems/double-a-number-represented-as-a-linked-list/?envType=daily-question&amp;amp;envId=2024-05-09&#34;&gt;&lt;ins class=&#34;dot&#34;&gt;È°åÁõÆÊïòËø∞&lt;/ins&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are given the  &lt;code&gt;head&lt;/code&gt;  of a &lt;strong&gt;non-empty&lt;/strong&gt; linked list representing a non-negative integer without leading zeroes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Return &lt;em&gt;the  &lt;code&gt;head&lt;/code&gt;  of the linked list after doubling it.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-1&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-1&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 1&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img data-src=&#34;https://assets.leetcode.com/uploads/2023/05/28/example.png&#34; alt=&#34;&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input:&lt;/strong&gt; head = [1,8,9]&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output:&lt;/strong&gt; [3,7,8]&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Explanation:&lt;/strong&gt; The figure above corresponds to the given linked list which represents the number 189. Hence, the returned linked list represents the number 189 * 2 = 378.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-2&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-2&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 2&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img data-src=&#34;https://assets.leetcode.com/uploads/2023/05/28/example2.png&#34; alt=&#34;&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input:&lt;/strong&gt; head = [9,9,9]&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output:&lt;/strong&gt; [1,9,9,8]&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Explanation:&lt;/strong&gt; The figure above corresponds to the given linked list which represents the number 999. Hence, the returned linked list reprersents the number 999 * 2 = 1998.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
